$ msg.exe

`msg.exe` is a *message utility* to send a message to a user.

{ Sending a message to oneself

  At times, it might be desired to send a message to oneself, for example in order ot get notified of a future event. Such a thing might be accomplished together with
  → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/schtasks_exe[`schtasks.exe`] (see for example → development/tools/scripts/personal/notify_me_at_bat[`notify_me_at.bat`] or
  → development/tools/scripts/personal/notif_ps1[`notif.ps1`]).
code {
C:\> schtasks … msg → Windows/development/environment-variables/USERNAME[%username%] water flowers
code }

}
{ Sending a message to all sessions

  Using a `*` sends the message to all → Windows/development/session[sessions] on a system.
code {
C:\> msg * birthday cake in 1st floor
code }

}

sa:
  → development/tools/scripts/personal/notify_me_at_bat[`notify_me_at.bat`]
